{
  "stem": "4963.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- well, and eventually he cried so hard with the-- with these Lithuanian people that they told him that he has to come and-- and pick him up because their lives were in danger.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were laws out that anyone who caught hiding a Jewish person or a child, the whole family would be annihilated, would be killed off.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they did make some examples of that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So, you know, they did actually catch people and -and killed off the whole family and had great publicity about that so that, you know, people wouldn't-- so that the Lithuanians or the Polish-descent people wouldn't be likely to do that.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he was brought back to the ghetto because he just was crying day and night, refused to eat, and, you know, they just--",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now I remember that they-- my Aunt Paula was very clever woman, and they had many friends, Lithuanian friends, so they kept plotting what to do, how to do.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they asked me, you know, they said, look, your family, Ceitlin family, was so well-known in that district.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Obviously you have people, you know, you know people.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Don't you know any one of your parents' friends who might hide you?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I really didn't know.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "However, that piano that I mentioned to you that my parents placed, the black grand piano with these Polish people, and I would go down there and practice so I said, well, I think I remember how to go to their house.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I remember them, so maybe they'll take me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So this was in 1940-- December-- it was either December 1943 of January 1944.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I-- they prepared me.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I was quite tall, and I remember it was big excitement.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
